modules.description: This module creates and manages a thread-unsafe client handle for logging messages through the Apple System Log. It supports configuring logging behavior with options like stderr output and connection settings, and allows adding file descriptors for directing log output with format and level controls. It is used to send structured logs to system log services on macOS with precise formatting and filtering.

This module constructs and manipulates log messages for the Apple System Log. It supports setting message attributes such as type, timestamp, host, sender, facility, and custom key-value pairs. Use it to create structured log entries with specific metadata for system logging on macOS.

This module implements logging to the Apple System Log on macOS, providing structured log message creation and submission with customizable metadata and severity levels. It includes a client interface for managing log connections and output settings, and a message builder for specifying log attributes like sender, facility, and key-value data. Use it to integrate macOS system logging with precise control over message formatting and delivery.

This module creates a log reporter that sends log messages to the Apple System Log (ASL) using a provided ASL client. It integrates directly with the `Logs` library, allowing applications to route log output to the system log facility on Apple platforms. Use this when building macOS or iOS applications that need to log messages to the system log for debugging or monitoring purposes.
